						<summary>

						<p>Chōḻa, Rājakēsarivarman Kulōttuṅga II, •••= A.D. 1138.</p>						

						<p>Badly worn out. The <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of a Chaturvēdimaṅgalam (name lost) is said to have made some temple land tax-free in lieu of some money that they had borrowed from the temple in the 15th year of Vikrama-chōḻa, that is in 1133. Most probably the purpose of the earlier borrowal was to pay off tax arrears (See No. 4 for comparison).</p>						

						</summary>
